    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for your feedback Sarah Sankey, Lead Nurse was sorry to learn that your experience was not as positive as we would have expected when you attended the Ambulatory Care Unit (ACU) at Manchester Royal Infirmary (MRI). It is important to us that comments are heard and seen as an opportunity for the service to make changes and improvements wherever possible. 

In response to your comments, we would like to reassure you that this feedback has been disseminated to all staff in the ACU and they have been reminded of the importance of effective and compassionate communication.

If you would like to discuss the matter further please contact our Patient Advice and Liaison Service (PALS) on 0161 276 8686 or by emailing pals@mft.nhs.uk they will be happy to discuss this with you, quoting reference PO19/0164.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
